# Project Conventions

## Stack

- React + TypeScript + Vite
- Modus Web Components: `@trimble-oss/moduswebcomponents-react` v1.3.0-react19
- Tailwind CSS v4 (utility classes only — do not re-create design tokens)

## Modus component compliance

**Always use Modus components for interactive UI.** Do not build custom `<button>`, `<input>`, or layout primitives when a Modus component exists.

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Any button / action | `ModusWcButton` + `onButtonClick` |
| Status indicators | `ModusWcBadge` |
| Page / card headings | `ModusWcTypography` |
| Content containers | `ModusWcCard` (with `bordered={false}`, `padding="compact"`) |
| Icons | `ModusWcIcon` (valid Modus icon names only) |
| Navbar | `ModusWcNavbar` — always present at app top |

**Reference page for correct patterns:** `financials-hub/src/pages/JobDetail.tsx`
- Uses `ModusWcCard`, `ModusWcTypography`, `ModusWcButton`, `ModusWcBadge` correctly
- Treat this as the in-repo standard; do not copy inline-styled period wizard pages for UI patterns

## Modus tokens — no hard-coded colours

Always use CSS variables, never hex values for UI chrome:

- `--modus-wc-color-base-page` / `base-100` / `base-200`
- `--modus-wc-color-base-content` / `base-content-low-contrast`
- `--modus-wc-color-primary`, `success`, `danger`, `warning`

## Events

- Buttons: `onButtonClick` (not raw `onClick` on `ModusWcButton`)
- Text inputs: `onInputChange` → value via `e.detail?.target?.value`
- Checkboxes / switches: `onInputChange` → `e.detail` is boolean

## Modus MCP — look up props before guessing

The `modus-docs` MCP server is configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`. Use it in Agent mode to verify component APIs:

- Pass `version: "1.3.0"` (the base package version from `package.json`)
- Ask: `get_modus_component_data` for component props/events/slots
- Ask: `get_modus_implementation_data` for React wiring guides

## Layout and structure

- Keep components small — extract logic into custom hooks
- Prefer named exports over default exports
- One primary (`filled` + primary) button per page section maximum
- Use `size="sm"` on `ModusWcButton`, `ModusWcBadge`, `ModusWcChip` by default
- Card title controls use `size="xs"`; navbar slot controls use `size="md"`
